the annapurna industries is dealing with manufacturing of corrugated box. as per information given by the branch , last year the sister concern m/s anslo autopack was slipped due to misutilization of working capital and non-compliance of issues received  in stock audit. during the whole year follow up for upgradation was done and  it reveal's that he is not in a position to repay our dues. the account is  transferred to arb and waiting for dm order .  now  in case of annapurna industries, last year the sales are very low and borrower is unable to repay the instalment. the borrower has shown inability to pay the instalment due to cash crunch. branch has issued many letters and made follow up with the borrower for repayment . he has also submitted request for restructuring and enhancement ,however borrower has not submitted any compliances of irregularities pointed out in stock audit by stock auditor . further, there are no sufficient transaction in cash credit account and also due to non availability of order in hands and non compliance of stock audit , enhancement request is not considered by the branch. further, borrower is not co-operating. even after several reminders and visits  made by dzm and cm arc and officials from zonal office along with chief manager, vadner bhairav,  every time the borrower behaved rudely and made inordinate delays for meeting with the executives from zo and not regularize their loan accounts although branch is ready for enhancement subject to confirm orders have to presented. borrower has not submitted the requisite documents till date.

visited m/s.shri gurudeo cotton processing company on 04.08.2023 along with branch manager rajura branch and shri, lakade patil sir (cm cpc) for recovery of overdue amount and up gradation of account and met with partner shri. sunil shantaram derkar. we discussed with mr. sunil derkar to repay the overdue amount approx.  of rs.12500000/- (overdue as of 31.08.2023) to upgrade the account. mr. sunil derkar told that during the peak season of ginning he met with major accident. so the factory was closed. he told that more than 3.50 crore was given to farmers as advance for procurement of raw material and same was not realized because of the factory is closed in peak season. he also told that subsidy amount of rs.64.00 lakhs is yet to release from maharashtra state govt and same may be received in the month of nov or dec-2023. as the activity is not started yet, he presently unable repay overdue amont.altough he assured to upgrade the account at earliest whenever season/ business activity started probably wef  nov 2023. we informed borrower that we are initiating legal proceedings for recovery of bank dues and also instructed to repay all overdues 11.08.2023.
